article.headline: Tulsa 67, SE Louisiana 52
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Steven Idlet made all nine of his shots from the field and scored 23 points Sunday to lead Tulsa to a 67-52 victory over Southeastern Louisiana. Idlet, a 6-foot-11 senior, had one 3-pointer among his field goals and went 4 for 6 from the free-throw line. Scottie Haralson was the only other player in double figures with 10 points for the Golden Hurricane (2-0), who never trailed in the game and led 33-20 at halftime. Brandon Fortenberry led the Lions (0-1) with 19 points. DeShawn Patterson added 11 points for Southeastern Louisiana.
